wiki.text:
'Doggie' (born April 19, 1966 in Køge) is a Danish artist, currently
based in Copenhagen and Istanbul.

He was one of the pioneers of Danish Hip-Hop and in the early 80's, he became a
member of The New Nation and started the graffiti crew The Dark Roses. He
studied advertising and worked as an AD and as a graphic designer since 1988.
He made several Hip-Hop jams, AV-shows and became involved in Scandinavian
graffiti exhibitions/shows as well. He lived and worked in Amsterdam, NYC and
Montpellier where he developed his 'tup' paintings and sculptures 'What you see
is what you get'.
